    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184/13</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Dr. <persName corresp="#p_MSE1" type="from">S. E.
                            Mezes</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-08">November 8,
                            1918</date>.<lb/>[Received November 11.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am writing to confirm a telegram
                    sent you to-day, in accordance with your request, reading as follows:<note
                        n="33" xml:id="d68fn33">For changes in this list of specialists, see Dr.
                            <persName corresp="#p_MSE1">Mezes</persName>’ letter of Nov. 14, 1918,
                        to Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName>, <ref
                            target="#pg_118">p. 118</ref>.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="flushleft">“Secretary of State,<lb/>Washington, D. C.</p>
                        <p>Belgium, <persName corresp="#p_HCH1">Haskins</persName>; Italy, <persName
                                corresp="#p_LWE1">Lunt</persName>; Russia, <persName
                                corresp="#p_LRH1">Lord</persName>; Turkey, <persName
                                corresp="#p_YAA1">Young</persName>; Austria-Hungary, <persName
                                corresp="#p_SC1">Seymour</persName>; Balkans, <persName
                                corresp="#p_DC1">Day</persName>; Colonies, <persName
                                corresp="#p_BGL1">Beer</persName>; Cartographers, <persName
                                corresp="#p_JM1">Jefferson</persName> and
                                <persName>Lobeck</persName>; Library, <persName corresp="#p_SJT1"
                                >Shotwell</persName>. An assistant for each specialist, making seven
                            assistants, would help very much.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MSE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">S. E. Mezes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
